</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Afro-textured hair</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">  (Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Wooly_hair_syndrome&amp;redirect=no" title="Wooly hair syndrome">Wooly hair syndrome</a>)</span></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Madagascan_Woman_(cropped).jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg/220px-Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg" width="220" height="315" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg/330px-Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg/440px-Madagascan_Woman_%28cropped%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="831" data-file-height="1189" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Madagascan_Woman_(cropped).jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Woman from the island of <a href="/wiki/Nosy_Be" title="Nosy Be">Nosy Be</a>, in <a href="/wiki/Madagascar" title="Madagascar">Madagascar</a>, c. 1868</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Afro-textured hair</b> is a term used to refer to the natural hair texture of certain populations in <a href="/wiki/Africa" title="Africa">Africa</a>, the <a href="/wiki/African_diaspora" title="African diaspora">African diaspora</a>, <a href="/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australia</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a>, when this hair has not been altered by <a href="/wiki/Hot_comb" title="Hot comb">hot combs</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iron_(appliance)" title="Iron (appliance)" class="mw-redirect">flat irons</a>, or chemicals (through <a href="/wiki/Perm_(hairstyle)" title="Perm (hairstyle)">perming</a>, <a href="/wiki/Relaxer" title="Relaxer">relaxation</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Hair_straightening" title="Hair straightening">straightening</a>). Each strand of this hair type grows in a tiny, spring-like <a href="/wiki/Helix" title="Helix">helix</a> shape. The overall effect is such that, despite relatively fewer hair shafts compared to <a href="/wiki/Straight_hair" title="Straight hair" class="mw-redirect">straight</a>, wavy or curly hair,<sup id="cite_ref-pmid11531795_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-pmid11531795-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> afro-textured hair appears and feels denser.</p>
<p></p>
